column5: What a way to start off the weekend lads!!....looks like you're all having a blast!!....sure am glad I haven't put the boat away yet!!

Wow, good work lads. Thats a mess of fish for only one day. How was the wind out there today? What was the average weight? Wish I was there, looks like its going to be a fun weekend. I will be checking in next thursday till sunday,can hardly wait.
Nice shooting guys !!!  I noticed Jose has the smallest fish !!!  Just saying..................  Sorry Jose. Couldn't resist taking a jab. Wish I could be on the boat with you dude.

Nice fish - No doubt about about it - Lloyd knows the waters... our charter with him this summer -  2 hours into the charter  he sayin' OK you got to let me know if its a keeper or release before we boat them, so we don't go over our limits - only a few of each left for us.
THATS INSANE WALLEYE FISHING!
Lol yes they are small but the put up a good fight
I'm not a Wally fisherman but I might have to change my mine, a buddy is always bugging to go for them, The Fish Gods sure are watching out for you Richard

This was such a great day with weather. Water was calm and the fish had wide open mouths all day long. It was nice to see Orange Peel team out on his boat relaxing and cooking some fish for lunch. Hope you get your big motor working and look forward to seeing you guys next year.
so that's what a BOQ eye looks like....
nice fish......
a good day indeed  ...so how about a story or two on the ten that got away???  very nice shootin guys
great day we went 23 for 33 great weather to just heading out for food here are some photos
A post and a phone call.. where is that bottle of El Dorado Deluxe Silver...
the score card
Great report Terry! FANTASTIC even! Nice pic of the Tyborski vessel as well...any news from them?
my baby
we know they caught fish we will talk to them in a little while at Guss restaurant
Good to hear Paul and Joey are joining you for supper. Must be lonely over there in the honeymoon suite at mouse turd resort...
Wow. It looks like the big girls are finally coming out to play
Excellent report and good shootin!  I think I should plan something for next year...
Man, looks like I missed an opertunity to fish with the master of BOQ. Well done byez

23 for 33.. we've never boated 23 fish in the full 3 or 4 days! I guess I'm the boat jinx and all this time we thought it was Terry!! .. oh wait.. maybe it's Dano.. he's not there either, poor bugger... surgery on Wednesday.
We do miss you guys  but all the fish made me forget every now and then
Hey stifle.  Not what I said,but ,,,,, Nice fish bud.
Boats in the water, cant wait for 5am  meet you at gus rest.
Wow .. nice Terry .. Loyd is definitely DA QUINTE MAN !
WOW!
Nice shootin!  Those are some nice Wallies!!!!!! Weather looks decent too. Congrats to you guys.
WOW you guys struck some nice gold Thanks for posting Terry Leechman
Wouldn't mind being a part of this some year.  Good to see the fish are cooperating the big ones are hungry.
If you leave now Rich..  you can be part of it by 6am !!!
10 hours .... yeah, I could make that.
I'm sure they'd be glad to have you aboard.. all you need is a bit of money and warm clothes.. get in the truck!
I'm there next year come hell or high water.If im missing an employee like this year,i'm gonna close the store for the weekend. Keep the pics coming i still have drool left.

Great day Terry, you guys sure did a number on Quinte...amazing! I wasnt sure of Loyd's boat-name markings but knew you would be out sometime this weekend We saw you just before our last troll,(We had an early day planned)... you folk were heading N/E towards Thompson's about 1/4 mile out and we were W/S/W, bound toward the cement plant in the black lund about 1;30 or so....you know what its like when the lines are out...Ya keep going!  My son and I went 4/6, and took home 3 for the pan. Sure looks like the big girls are in....  WTG on a successful day Terry.  -Pete  edit: Real nice pic of the Tybo's new boat, love the mast too!  edit 2: I had on the old OFC yeller jacket, its s till in good shape lol.
